oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Capture of the H.M. ships Cyane and Levant
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: A colored print P.S. Dural Litha. Philadelphia. Original Painting by Birch. Shows three ships on dark waters and under cloudy sky. There is light and smoke around the ships from gunfire. Additional information on back of print. "Capture of H.M.Ships Cyane & Levant by the U.S. frigate Consitution. To Cas. Stewart Esq. His Officers & Crew." "Levant 21 Guns" "Constitution 49 Guns" "Cyane 34 Guns" "Un soone Ty Jas. Queen"
